                                            We're getting downright musical with the first one.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Not sure how to get the most out of your Linux device? This weekend, I'm back with another set of free and open source apps Linux fans will want to try installing. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 12:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-apps-to-try-september-19/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Overlooked Windows 11 Privacy Upgrade That Just Works]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-overlooked-windows-privacy-upgrade-that-just-works/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Rich Hein]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/illustration-of-encrypted-dns-with-a-key-and-padlock-icons-connected-to-a-block-of-encrypted-text.png" length="1135" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Privacy]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cybersecurity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Unencrypted DNS exposes every site you visit. Here's how to encrypt it to keep your browsing private from ISPs and prying eyes.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>For a long time, I never thought about what happens when I type a web address into a browser and hit “Enter.” In fact, your computer asks a DNS server where to find the site, and unless you’ve previously made changes to your settings, that request goes out in plain text, visible to any system your traffic passes through on its way across the network.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 12:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-overlooked-windows-privacy-upgrade-that-just-works/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The American Electric Sedan That Finally Puts Range Anxiety to Rest]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/american-electric-sedan-finally-puts-range-anxiety-to-rest/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/gtlaunch_gtp_quantumgrey_track_side2.jpg" length="275" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This American electric sedan sets a range record, making long trips possible without the stress of constant charging.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/category/electric-vehicles/" target="_blank">Electric vehicles (EVs)</a> deliver instant power, futuristic tech, and the bonus of zero tailpipe emissions. Still, range is the factor that matters most.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 11:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/american-electric-sedan-finally-puts-range-anxiety-to-rest/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[If You Put a Case On Your iPhone Air, I'm Calling You Out]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/if-you-put-a-case-on-your-iphone-air-im-calling-you-out/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-air-camera-plateau.jpg" length="907" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone Air]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro Max]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The line between genius and madness is thin indeed.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>As you're reading this, presumably millions of people have an iPhone Air in their hands, as Apple's latest thinness-obsessed product hits the phone market. I hope you like it, I really hope this sliver of titanium and glass is everything you hoped it would be—but if you dare put a case on it, know that I'm judging you hard.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 11:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/if-you-put-a-case-on-your-iphone-air-im-calling-you-out/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Razer’s Thunderbolt 5 Dock Chroma Is Almost The Perfect Hub For Me]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/razer-thunderbolt-5-dock-chroma-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/a7308478.jpg" length="557" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Razer Thunderbolt 5 Dock]]></category><category><![CDATA[USB-C]]></category><category><![CDATA[USB]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            With a price tag of $400, the Razer Thunderbolt 5 Dock Chroma promises to be the ultimate hub. But does it deliver?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I’ve used Thunderbolt docks for nearly a decade at this point, going all the way back to my 2016 15-inch MacBook Pro when Apple finally went all-in on USB-C. I’ve spent the past few weeks with <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FDMLTDB3?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2016525&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Frazer-thunderbolt-5-dock-chroma-review%2F&asc_campaign=Authority" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow sponsored" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Razer’s all-new Thunderbolt 5 Dock Chroma</a>, and this is the best Thunderbolt dock I’ve ever used—with two catches.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/razer-thunderbolt-5-dock-chroma-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[3 Disney+ Shows You Can Knock Out in a Weekend (Sept. 19 - 21)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/disney-plus-shows-weekend-binge-september-21/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Derek Malcolm]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/disney-logo-with-a-film-strip-curling-around-it.png" length="1119" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Disney+]]></category><category><![CDATA[Weekend]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Disney+ offers some of the best universes and characters to escape into this weekend.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I just can't quit <a href="https://disneyplus.bn5x.net/c/156932/564546/9358?subId1=UUhtgUeUpU2016681&subId2=ehtg&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.disneyplus.com%2F" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Disney+</a>. I initially subscribed to the service back in the day to have all the major Star Wars, Marvel, and Pixar stuff at my fingertips. Still, the service has managed to surprise me with easily bingeable shows and docuseries that I didn't know I needed.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 19 Sep 2025 05:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/disney-plus-shows-weekend-binge-september-21/</guid></item></channel>
